\begin_layout Subsection*
Abstract:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The article discusses the use of Partial Least Squares Structural Equation
 Modeling (PLS-SEM) in construction management research.
 The technique has been increasingly adopted in this field over the last
 two decades.
 The paper critically reviews 139 articles that applied PLS-SEM from 2002
 to 2019.
 It highlights the use and misuse of PLS-SEM in the construction management
 area and provides recommendations for its future application.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*
Introduction:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The introduction emphasizes the extensive application of Structural Equation
 Modeling (SEM) across various research disciplines since the early 1980s.
 PLS-SEM, an alternative to covariance-based SEM, focuses on maximizing
 the explained variance of dependent latent constructs.
 The application of PLS-SEM in construction management is relatively new.
\end_layout

