\begin_layout Standard
The article critically examines the reasons for choosing Partial Least Squares
 Structural Equation Modeling (PLS-SEM) in construction management research.
 The reasons and motivations for adopting PLS-SEM are diverse, and the article
 provides a comprehensive breakdown:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Small Sample Size (58.27% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM is particularly
 suitable for datasets with a small sample size.
 This is one of the most frequently cited reasons for its adoption.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Non-Normal Data (40.29% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM can handle datasets
 that do not follow a normal distribution, making it a preferred choice
 in such scenarios.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Initiation of Exploratory Research (31.65% of the reviewed articles): For
 research that is exploratory in nature, PLS-SEM is often chosen due to
 its ability to handle formative measures and its focus on prediction.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Formative Measures (16.55% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM is suitable
 for datasets with formative measures, which are variables that form or
 cause the latent variable.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Focus on Prediction (14.39% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM emphasizes
 maximizing the explained variance of dependent latent constructs, making
 it ideal for predictive modeling.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Model Complexity (14.39% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM can estimate
 complex relationships and is often chosen for its ability to handle intricate
 models.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Theory Development (7.19% of the reviewed articles): Some researchers adopt
 PLS-SEM when their primary objective is to develop new theories.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Theory Validation (6.47% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM is also used
 when the aim is to validate existing theories.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Use of Categorical Variables (5.04% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM can
 handle categorical variables, making it suitable for datasets with such
 variables.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Addressing the Mediation Effect (4.32% of the reviewed articles): PLS-SEM
 is chosen when researchers aim to address or study the mediation effect
 in their models.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Not Specified (7.91% of the reviewed articles): Some articles did not specify
 any particular reason for using PLS-SEM.
\end_layout

